ProtoResult:
. "Suppose that $ |f(x)|\le M, a\le x\le b, $ and let $P'$ be 
   a partition of $[a,b]$ obtained by adding $r$ points to a 
   partition $P=\{x_0,x_1, $\dots$,x_n\}$ of $[a,b]$ Then $$ 
   S(P)\ge S(P')\ar\ge S(P)-2Mr\|P\|\\ and \\ s(P)\le 
   s(P')\ar\le s(P)+2Mr\|P\|. $$"
